Context:
The following fees are applicable to full-time students at George Brown College for the 2023/2024 terms:

- $10,762.50 due on June 12, 2023
- $6,804.70 due on June 12, 2023
- $4,082.80 due on November 9, 2023
- $4,101.60 due on June 12, 2023 and September 25, 2023
- $2,734.00 due on January 22, 2024
- $5,381.25 due on December 4, 2023

Students can pay through My Housing Portal using MasterCard, Visa or major Canadian banks. They may also courier payment in the form of a certified cheque/money order and make it payable to "CLC George Brown". The address for couriered payments is 80 Cooperage St, Toronto ON, M5A 0J3 Attn To: Residence Manager.

Students are advised not to confuse the "George Brown College Residence" payee with the one reserved for tuition fees. Payments will not be notified upon receipt. Students can check their account information on the Portal under the tab “Accounts”. For wire transfer information, they can email info@georgebrownresidence.ca.

The college application deadlines, news, events, tours and more can be kept up-to-date by signing up on the website. The contact details are 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559 and ask.george@georgebrown.ca.
